update configure and build system

re-automake/autoconf/autogen

Problem: There have been changes to configure.ac.  The
build system needs to be regenerated.

Run ./autogen.sh to regenerate everything.

configure: update AM_INIT_AUTOMAKE

Problem: The current use of AM_INIT_AUTOMAKE is obsolete.

Update usage of AM_INIT_AUTOMAKE, but there are many fallouts from this.

Remove use of META file, AC_META, and remove ac_meta.m4.
Update use of macros in genders.spec.in.

config: replace AC_HELP_STRING with AS_HELP_STRING

Problem: The autoconf macro AC_HELP_STRING is obsolete.

Update to AS_HELP_STRING.

configure: update obsolete AM_CONFIG_HEADER

Problem: AM_CONFIG_HEADER is obsolete.

Replace with AC_CONFIG_HEADERS.

Merge pull request #53 from chu11/build_update

workflow: add basic github workflow

workflow: add basic sanity build workflow

Problem: There's no basic build and test for genders.

Add a basic build and test workflow.

re-automake/autoconf/autogen

Problem: There have been changes to Makefile.am and configure.ac.  The
build system needs to be regenerated.

Run ./autogen.sh to regenerate everything.

Makefile.am: add make check target

Problem: There is no make check target for the libgenders tests.

Add a make check target in the root Makefile.am.

configure: default java extensions to be off

Problem: The location of jni.h is very distro and version dependent.
The build does not work by default on many modern systems.

Do not default java extensions to be built.

configure.ac: update python to python3

Problem: configure defaults to looking for python, which isn't as common
on modern distros.

Look for "python3" instead.
configure.ac: remove some trailing whitespace

Fix various typos found by crate-ci typo checker.

Fix genders_nodelist_destroy.3 man page

Prior to this it tried to recursively link to itself, leading to:
/usr/share/man/man3/genders_nodelist_destroy.3:27: can't open `man3/genders_nodelist_destroy.3': No such file or directory
